### Importing an application deployed from a local charm

The controller does not record the local archive file, so on import only
`local_charm.name`, `base`, and `origin_hash` are populated. You must set
`local_charm.path` in your configuration (an in-place update) before the next
`terraform plan`/`apply`.

```hcl
resource "juju_application" "my_local_charm" {
  model_uuid = juju_model.development.uuid
  local_charm {
    name = "my-local-charm"
    path = "${path.module}/my-local-charm.charm" # the archive originally deployed
    base = "ubuntu@22.04"
  }
}
```


## Note on Subordinate Applications and Units
For subordinate applications (such as those that attach to a principal charm). Starting with version 0.19.0, remove the units field from your subordinate application.

The provider will show units = 1 in state for subordinates if the units field is omitted, this is expected and for backwards compatibility.